definition.value: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of the 2- and 3-sulfate groups of the polysulfates of cellulose and charonin.

Catalysis of the reaction -  4-deoxy-beta-D-gluc-4-enuronosyl-(1--gt-3)-N-acetyl-D-galactosamine 4-sulfate + H(2)O -eq- 4-deoxy-beta-D-gluc-4-enuronosyl-(1--gt-3)-N-acetyl-D-galactosamine + H(+) + sulfate.

Catalysis of the reaction -  4-deoxy-beta-D-gluc-4-enuronosyl-(1--gt-3)-N-acetyl-D-galactosamine 6-sulfate + H(2)O -eq- 4-deoxy-beta-D-gluc-4-enuronosyl-(1--gt-3)-N-acetyl-D-galactosamine + H(+) + sulfate.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of the 3-sulfate groups of the N-sulfo-D-glucosamine 3-O-sulfate units of heparin.
Catalysis of the exonucleolytic cleavage that removes extra residues from the 3'-terminus of tRNA to produce 5'-mononucleotides.
Catalysis of the endonucleolytic cleavage to give 5'-phosphooligonucleotide end-products, with a preference for cleavage within the sequence CC.
Catalysis of the endonucleolytic cleavage near pyrimidine dimers to products with 5'-phosphate.
Catalysis of the endonucleolytic cleavage of poly(A) to fragments terminated by 3'-hydroxy and 5'-phosphate groups.
Catalysis of the endonucleolytic cleavage of RNA, removing 3'-extranucleotides from tRNA precursor.
Catalysis of the endonucleolytic cleavage of poly(U) to fragments terminated by 3'-hydroxy and 5'-phosphate groups.
Catalysis of the endonucleolytic cleavage of poly(U) or poly(C) to fragments terminated by 3'-hydroxy and 5'-phosphate groups.
Catalysis of the two-stage endonucleolytic cleavage to nucleoside 3'-phosphates and 3'-phosphooligonucleotides with 2',3'-cyclic phosphate intermediates.
Catalysis of the endonucleolytic cleavage to 2',3'-cyclic nucleotides.
Catalysis of the two-stage endonucleolytic cleavage to nucleoside 3'-phosphates and 3'-phosphooligonucleotides ending in Ap or Gp with 2',3'-cyclic phosphate intermediates.
Catalysis of the endonucleolytic cleavage of RNA precursor into two, leaving 5'-hydroxy and 3'-phosphate groups.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of poly(A), forming oligoribonucleotides and ultimately 3'-AMP.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of the phosphodiester linkage between guanosine and adenosine residues at one specific position in 28S rRNA from rat ribosomes.
Catalysis of the endohydrolysis of 1,6-alpha-D-glucosidic linkages in dextran.
Catalysis of the random hydrolysis of (1--gt-3)-beta-D-glycosidic linkages in (1--gt-3)-beta-D-xylans.
Catalysis of the random hydrolysis of 1,3-linkages between beta-D-glucuronate and N-acetyl-D-glucosamine residues in hyaluronate.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of terminal non-reducing beta-D-fucose residues in beta-D-fucosides.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of terminal, non-reducing beta-L-rhamnose residues in beta-L-rhamnosides.
Catalysis of the endohydrolysis of 1,2-alpha-L-fucoside linkages in fucoidan without release of sulfate.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of (1--gt-4)-alpha-D-glucosidic linkages in amylaceous polysaccharides, to remove successive maltotetraose residues from the non-reducing chain ends.
Catalysis of the endohydrolysis of 1,4-alpha-D-glucosidic linkages in alpha-D-glucans containing both 1,3- and 1,4-bonds.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of (2--gt-6)-beta-D-fructofuranan, to remove successive disaccharide residues as levanbiose, i.e. 6-(beta-D-fructofuranosyl)-D-fructose, from the end of the chain.
Catalysis of the random hydrolysis of (1--gt-2)-glucosidic linkages in (1--gt-2)-beta-D-glucans.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of successive xylose residues from the non-reducing termini of (1--gt-3)-beta-D-xylans.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of (1--gt-2) and (1--gt-3) linkages in mannan, releasing mannose.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of (1--gt-4)-beta-D-galactosidic linkages in agarose, giving the tetramer as the predominant product.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of pectic acid from the non-reducing end, releasing digalacturonate.
Catalysis of the endohydrolysis of 1,4-beta-D-linkages between D-galactose 4-sulfate and 3,6-anhydro-D-galactose in kappa-carrageenans.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of terminal (1--gt-3)-alpha-D-glucosidic links in 1,3-alpha-D-glucans.
Catalysis of the reaction -  a 6-phospho-beta-D-galactoside + H2O -eq- 6-phospho-D-galactose + an alcohol.
Catalysis of the random hydrolysis of (1--gt-3)-alpha-D-galactosidic linkages in Aerobacter aerogenes capsular polysaccharide.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of terminal, non-reducing N-acetylmuramic residues.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of (1--gt-6)-alpha-D-glucosidic linkages in polysaccharides, to remove successive isomaltose units from the non-reducing ends of the chains.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of (1--gt-6)-alpha-D-glucosidic linkages in dextrans, to remove successive isomaltotriose units from the non-reducing ends of the chains.

Catalysis of the endohydrolysis of the N,N'-diacetylchitobiosyl unit in high-mannose glycopeptides and glycoproteins containing the -[Man(GlcNAc)2]Asn-structure. One N-acetyl-D-glucosamine residue remains attached to the protein -  the rest of the oligosaccharide is released intact.
Catalysis of the reaction -  D-galactosyl-3-(N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosaminyl)-L-serine + H2O -eq- D-galactosyl-3-N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosamine + L-serine.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of (1--gt-4)-alpha-D-glucosidic linkages in amylaceous polysaccharides, to remove successive maltohexaose residues from the non-reducing chain ends.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of (1--gt-4)-beta-D-mannosidic linkages in (1--gt-4)-beta-D-mannans, to remove successive mannobiose residues from the non-reducing chain ends.
Catalysis of the endohydrolysis of (1--gt-4)-beta-D-galactosidic linkages in blood group A and B substances.
Catalysis of the endohydrolysis of (1--gt-4)-beta-D-galactosidic linkages in keratan sulfate.
Catalysis of the endohydrolysis of (1--gt-4)-alpha-D-galactosaminidic linkages in poly(D-galactosamine).
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of (1--gt-3) linkages between alpha-L-fucose and N-acetylglucosamine residues in glycoproteins.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of (1--gt-2)-alpha-D-glucosidic linkages at the branch points of dextrans and related polysaccharides, producing free D-glucose.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of (1--gt-4)-alpha-D-glucosidic linkages in amylaceous polysaccharides, to remove successive maltotriose residues from the non-reducing chain ends.

Catalysis of the hydrolysis of (1--gt-4)-beta-D-glucosidic links in oligoxyloglucans so as to remove successive isoprimeverose (i.e. alpha-xylo-1,6-beta-D-glucosyl-) residues from the non-reducing chain ends.
Catalysis of the endohydrolysis of the D-mannuronide linkages of polymannuronate.
